---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "@/config/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - Thejands"
  description="Terms governing use of the Thejands website and general conditions applicable to our professional services engagements."
  keywords="Thejands terms of service, terms and conditions, professional services terms, software development agreement"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: "Home", item: "https://thejands.in" },
    { name: "Terms of Service", item: "https://thejands.in/terms" },
  ]}
>
  <article
    class="section-spacing mx-auto max-w-[var(--max-width-content)] px-6"
  >
    <h1 class="font-display text-display-lg text-ink mt-0">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-body-sm text-mute">Last updated: 23 May 2026</p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the Thejands website
      at <a href="https://thejands.in" class="underline underline-offset-4"
        >thejands.in</a
      > (the "Site"), operated by Thejands, a professional services firm incorporated
      and operating in Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India. Please read these Terms carefully
      before using the Site.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      These Terms apply to the Site only. Where Thejands provides software
      development, technology consulting, or other professional services to a
      client, those services are governed exclusively by the applicable
      Statement of Work, Engagement Letter, or Master Services Agreement signed
      between Thejands and that client. In the event of any conflict between
      these Terms and a signed engagement agreement, the engagement agreement
      prevails.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      1. Acceptance of Terms
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      By accessing or using the Site in any way - including browsing pages,
      submitting a contact form, or sharing a link - you agree to be bound by
      these Terms. If you do not agree with any part of these Terms, please
      discontinue use of the Site immediately.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      These Terms apply to all visitors, prospective clients, recruiters,
      partners, and any other parties who access the Site. Use of the Site is
      subject to applicable local laws and regulations; it is your
      responsibility to ensure that accessing this Site is lawful in your
      jurisdiction.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      2. Nature of the Site and Our Services
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      The Site is a marketing and informational website. It describes Thejands'
      capabilities, approach, team, and areas of expertise. Nothing on this Site
      constitutes an offer capable of acceptance or a binding commitment to
      provide any service.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Thejands provides enterprise software development, technology consulting,
      digital product delivery, and related professional services. All such
      services are scoped, priced, and formalised through individually
      negotiated Statements of Work or Engagement Letters. No services are
      provided through or on the basis of these Terms alone.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Thejands operates on fixed-scope, milestone-based contracts. Project terms
      including deliverables, timelines, payment schedules, and acceptance
      criteria are defined within the relevant engagement documentation and are
      binding only upon execution of that documentation by both parties.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      3. Intellectual Property
    </h2>
    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">
      3a. Website Content
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      All content on this Site - including but not limited to text, design,
      graphics, logos, case study summaries, and code - is the intellectual
      property of Thejands or its licensors and is protected under applicable
      copyright, trademark, and intellectual property laws. All rights are
      reserved.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      You may view, print, and share individual pages of the Site for personal,
      non-commercial reference purposes. You may not reproduce, republish,
      scrape, sell, sublicense, or use Site content for commercial purposes
      without our prior written consent.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">
      3b. Client Engagement IP
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Intellectual property created by Thejands in the course of a client
      engagement - including source code, architecture designs, documentation,
      and other deliverables - transfers to the client upon receipt of full
      payment as specified in the applicable engagement agreement. Prior to full
      payment, all such IP remains owned by Thejands. The precise IP assignment
      terms, including any licence grants, retained rights, and open-source
      component disclosures, are set out in the relevant Statement of Work or
      Engagement Letter.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      4. Confidentiality
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Thejands treats all confidential information shared by prospective and
      active clients with strict confidentiality. We do not share, publish, or
      disclose client information, project details, or proprietary business data
      to any third party without consent, except as required by law.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      For active engagements, both Thejands and the client execute a mutual
      Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) before any substantive confidential
      information is exchanged. The NDA governs confidentiality obligations
      during and after the engagement. Information submitted via the contact
      form on this Site is handled in accordance with our <a
        href="/privacy"
        class="underline underline-offset-4">Privacy Policy</a
      >, not under a formal NDA (unless a separate NDA is subsequently agreed).
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      5. Limitation of Liability
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      The Site and all content on it are provided on an "as is" and "as
      available" basis without any warranty of any kind, express or implied,
      including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability,
      fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy, or non-infringement.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Thejands, its founders,
      employees, and agents shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental,
      consequential, special, exemplary, or punitive damages arising out of or
      in connection with your use of - or inability to use - this Site or any
      content on it. This includes, without limitation, damages for loss of
      profits, business, data, goodwill, or other intangible losses, even if
      Thejands has been advised of the possibility of such damages.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      In no event shall Thejands' total liability to you for any claim arising
      out of your use of this Site exceed INR 1,000 (Indian Rupees One
      Thousand). This limitation reflects that the Site is an informational
      resource provided free of charge.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Liability arising from professional services engagements is governed by
      the limitation of liability clauses in the applicable Statement of Work or
      Engagement Letter, not by these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      6. Third-Party Links
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      This Site may contain hyperlinks to external websites operated by third
      parties, including technology partners, open-source projects, or reference
      resources. These links are provided for convenience only. Thejands does
      not control, endorse, or accept responsibility for the content, privacy
      practices, or terms of any external website.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Clicking any external link is done at your own risk. We encourage you to
      read the privacy policies and terms of any third-party sites you visit.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">7. Disclaimers</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      All content on this Site is provided for general informational and
      marketing purposes only. It does not constitute - and should not be relied
      upon as - legal, financial, investment, tax, or any other form of
      professional advice. You should seek independent professional advice
      before making any decisions based on information on this Site.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Descriptions of services, capabilities, technologies, or processes on this
      Site are general in nature and may not reflect the precise scope,
      approach, or deliverables for any specific engagement. All engagements are
      individually scoped and documented.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Thejands makes reasonable efforts to keep Site content accurate and up to
      date, but we make no representations or warranties that information on the
      Site is complete, accurate, current, or error-free. We reserve the right
      to modify or remove content at any time without notice.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      8. Prohibited Use
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">You agree not to use the Site to:</p>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Scrape, crawl, or systematically extract content for commercial use
        without written consent
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Submit false, misleading, or fraudulent information through any form
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the Site's
        infrastructure
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Transmit spam, malware, or any content that is unlawful, harmful, or
        offensive
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Use the Site in any way that violates applicable laws or regulations in
        your jurisdiction
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      9. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      These Terms and any disputes arising out of or in connection with them or
      your use of this Site shall be governed by and construed in accordance
      with the laws of the Republic of India, without regard to its conflict of
      law provisions.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      The courts of Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India shall have exclusive jurisdiction
      over any disputes arising under or in connection with these Terms, subject
      to your right to seek injunctive or other equitable relief in any
      competent court where necessary to protect your rights.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      For clients in the UK, EU, US, Singapore, or UAE, disputes relating to
      professional services engagements are governed by the dispute resolution
      clause in the applicable engagement agreement, which may provide for
      alternative dispute resolution mechanisms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      10. Changes to These Terms
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Thejands reserves the right to modify these Terms at any time. Changes
      will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Material
      changes will be indicated clearly. Your continued use of the Site after
      changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms. If you do
      not agree to the updated Terms, you should cease using the Site.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">11. Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us:
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      <strong>Thejands</strong><br />
      Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India<br />
      Email: <a
        href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contact.email}`}
        class="underline underline-offset-4">{siteConfig.contact.email}</a
      >
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
